{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_152","type":"agent_message","text":"`jakarta.inject.Provider` and `kotlinx.coroutines.reactor.MonoKt` don’t show up as Spring Kafka-owned probes in the library bytecode; they’re coming from framework-level optional checks exercised by the tests. I’m moving those two entries out of published metadata and into test-local metadata so `checkMetadataFiles` passes without weakening the native test coverage."}}
